Networking and Sysadmin Skills you gain:
# Technical Skills`
`Networking Knowledge:`

Understanding of network protocols (TCP/IP, DNS, DHCP, etc.)
Network configuration and troubleshooting
Managing routers, switches, firewalls, and other network devices
Network security principles and practices
Operating Systems:

Proficiency in managing various operating systems (Windows, Linux, macOS)
System installation, configuration, and maintenance
User and group management
File system management and permissions
Server Management:

Configuring and maintaining servers (web servers, database servers, mail servers, etc.)
Virtualization technologies (VMware, Hyper-V, etc.)
Cloud services and platforms (AWS, Azure, Google Cloud)
Backup and disaster recovery planning
Security:

Implementing and managing security policies and procedures
Antivirus and anti-malware solutions
Intrusion detection and prevention systems
Encryption and data protection methods
Scripting and Automation:

Writing scripts to automate repetitive tasks (PowerShell, Bash, Python)
Understanding automation tools and frameworks (Ansible, Puppet, Chef)
Monitoring and logging automation
Troubleshooting and Problem-Solving:

Identifying and resolving hardware and software issues
Network diagnostic tools (ping, tracert, netstat)
Analyzing system logs and event management
Non-Technical Skills
Communication:

Clearly communicating technical information to non-technical users
Writing technical documentation and reports
Collaborating with other IT professionals and departments
Time Management and Organization:

Prioritizing tasks and managing time effectively
Handling multiple projects and incidents simultaneously
Documenting configurations and changes
Customer Service:

Providing excellent support to end-users
Understanding and addressing user needs and concerns
Maintaining a positive and patient attitude
Analytical Thinking:

Analyzing system performance and identifying areas for improvement
Conducting risk assessments and impact analyses
Developing and implementing effective solutions
Project Management:

Planning and executing IT projects
Budgeting and resource allocation
Meeting project deadlines and milestones
Adaptability and Continuous Learning:

Staying updated with the latest technologies and industry trends
Adapting to new tools, systems, and processes
Pursuing certifications and professional development opportunities
Common Certifications
CompTIA Network+
CompTIA Security+
Cisco Certified Network Associate (CCNA)
Microsoft Certified: Azure Administrator Associate
Certified Information Systems Security Professional (CISSP)
Red Hat Certified System Administrator (RHCSA)
Amazon Web Services (AWS) Certified Solutions Architect
